whenever i am stressed out or sad, i will visit cuteoverload for a dose of cute junkies. It works for me, in the past, and now too. :>  

Source: Cuteoverload

1. Know your blood pressure. Have it checked regularly.
  2. Know what your weight should be. Keep it at or below that level.
  3. Don't use too much salt in cooking or at meals. Avoid salty foods.
  4. Eat a diet rich in fruits, vegetables and whole-grain high-fiber foods according to American Heart Association recommendations.
  5. Control alcohol intake. Don't have more than one drink a day if you're a woman or two a day if you're a man.
  6. Take your medicine exactly as prescribed. Don't run out of pills even for a single day.
  7. Keep appointments with the doctor.
  8. Follow your doctor's advice about physical activity.
  9. Make certain your parents, brothers, sisters and children have their blood pressure checked regularly.
  10. Live a normal life in every other way.
++++++++++++++++
I really hope everyone takes good care of their own health and for those around them, please give them your support and love.

I've been down with flu, cough.. And you know what, i've been really fickle lately.. especially when dealing with money issues. Should i go overseas in DEC or save a more bit more for my post-poned grad trip. Oh wellls... it all boils down to me not wanting to spend my hard earned savings.. 

Had plenty of rest at home, and i'm quite bascially doing nothing and i'm feeling guilty...

My colleague recommended me to visit this Marutama Ra-men at the Central. Ordered the chicken soup based ramen with an additional order of seasoned egg (quite a clever selling technique). I was pretty excited as my colleague told me it was the best she ever eaten here in SG.. So, with "high expectation". I was pretty disappointed upon the presentation of the ramen as you can see below.. But it is not as important as the taste i would say. The ambience of the restaurant kinda make up for the presentation.



The noodle in the thick broth was really tangy. :> The seasoned egg was REALLY REALLY nice... it looks like hard boiled egg on the outside and you don't really expect the yolk inside to be in bright orange colour with jelly-like texture. The seasoned egg tasted really unique and for that moment i would want to get hold of the recipe. :>. The simplicity of the ra-men is to bring out the flavour of such common food like eggs. Tried the gyoza, the skin was really thin and smooth and the fillings was fresh! yumms.. it came with lots of vinegar and I LOVE vinegar.. and i don't have to like dip my gyoza in those small dishes. SIMPLY love it.

Priced at 12 bucks..seasoned egg at 1 buck.. gyoza at 5 bucks, i feel that the ra-men was definitely more pricey compared to the others, but the ambience was relaxing and the chefs are Jap..and they all speak Jap kinda feel myself in Jap.. lol :>

Jack and I have been anticipating for Pixar's newest creation... Wall-e And i can say our wait was worth it AGAIN! :> It is definitely more than Robots with human emotions. You guys should catch it to know more! Is a show that goes beyond all languages and culture as there is little dialogue.. Is really hard to make a movie with a meaningful message to get through to us! When i was watching the show, i was brimming with emotions. Emotions that overwhelmed me. Those little gestures in the movie were really heart warming, cute and nice. You've got to watch it to understand what i really means. So.. 2 thumbs up for Wall -e!!

My first week in the working society! officially! not temp job or whatsoever. Time to build your reputation, your career path etc etc. How fun is that!?

Anyway my team consists of peepz from ntu/nus. In fact, one of my colleagues is actually Jack's game development friend's gf in NUS! How nice! so yea, we hit it off, and i hope it will last. Yea, so for the first week i'm still adapting to the environment, alright so far. 

For my weekend, i organized my JC bbq gathering, and it went out well! 3/4 of the class turn up! So happy about it! Grace even said that i signed on for being JC class rep for life. But is okay.. once in a while is kinda fun. 

a taste of hows full-time work like for a week, i've to re-schedule a lot of things, juggle more things because i never see myself as a workaholic. In fact my goal is to be a person living a well balanced life. I will not never feel proud being a workaholic because it just show that i am missing out on a lot of things in life. I guess the few aspects like personal time, bf relationship, friendship, family, hobbies, new skill, the hardest to juggle probably is friendship and bf relationship. If it happens that your bf or friends are career minded, workaholic bunch of people, it requires 2 hands to make a clap.  So probably.. is about having the right mindset and the right techniques! 

All the best to those who are already in the working society!
